types of req:

implicit: openid://?response_type=id_token
              &client_id=https://rp.example.com/cb
              &scope=openid did_authn
              &request= <Request Object / JWT>

auth_code: openid://?response_type=code
               &client_id=https://rp.example.com/cb
               &scope=openid did_authn
               &request= <Request Object / JWT>

auth_code:  openid://?response_type=id_token
           			    &grant_type=authorization_code
               &code=AUTHORIZATION_CODE
               &client_id=https://rp.example.com/cb_id_token
               &scope=openid did_authn
               &request= <Request Object / JWT (request object used previously)>


1. RP: GENERATE REQUEST
send {response_type:'code'} as options parameter. default is 'id_token'

2. Provider : Validate Request (validate_request method)
returns an object with response_type

3. Provider check response_type of request and generate response accordingly




